page.title: 09Deerfold Wood Wadborough.
page.content: In Wadborogh we saw quite a lot of wildlife in the wood .In Deerfold wood we saw a few animals and ground birds such as{pheasants}and{partridges .The name Deerfold wood indicates that there might have been{deer}in wood at one time but we could not see any signs of them. We found some{rabbit burrows in the wood and we found a shell of a hazel nut that had been partly eaten by a{wood vole.}We also found some{fox}tracks and think we saw a{fox.}We saw two{partridges,}a male and a female. In the grass we saw what we think was a{grass snake}. In the trees there was a{grey squirrel}so if it was not a{wood vole}that ate the hazel nut it could of been a{squirrel.
